---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const updated = '2026-06-11';
---

<Base
    title="Terms & Conditions | PediaCare"
    description="Terms of use for PediaCare: educational content only, no medical advice, no doctor-patient relationship, generic active ingredients without dosages."
>
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Terms & Conditions' }]} />

    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 py-8 space-y-6">
        <header class="space-y-1">
            <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-4xl font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF] tracking-tight">Terms & Conditions</h1>
            <p class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 dark:text-[#8B84B8]">Last updated: {updated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-night-card rounded-3xl border border-orange-100 dark:border-night-line shadow-premium p-6 md:p-8 space-y-5 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-[#D8D2F5] font-medium leading-relaxed">
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">1. Educational purpose only</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    All content on PediaCare is provided for general educational purposes. It is
                    not medical advice, does not establish a doctor–patient relationship, and must
                    not be used as a substitute for examination, diagnosis, or treatment by a
                    qualified healthcare professional.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">2. Emergencies</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Never delay seeking professional care because of something read here. If your
                    child may be experiencing an emergency, call your local emergency number
                    immediately.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">3. Medication information</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Profiles list generic active ingredients only — never brands and never doses.
                    Pediatric dosing depends on weight, age, and history and must come from your
                    child's clinician or pharmacist. Never administer self-designed therapies.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">4. Accuracy and currency</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    We aim to align content with reputable guidance (AAP, CDC, WHO, NHS) and
                    welcome corrections, but medicine evolves and errors are possible. Content is
                    provided "as is" without warranties of completeness or fitness for a
                    particular purpose.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">5. Limitation of liability</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    To the maximum extent permitted by law, PediaCare and its contributors accept
                    no liability for decisions made or actions taken based on this site's content.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">6. Intellectual property</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Text and illustrations are © PediaCare unless otherwise noted. You may share
                    excerpts with attribution for non-commercial educational use.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </article>
</Base>
